* {{flag|Czech Republic}}: The ''<U+00DA>tvar Rychl<U+00E9>ho Nasazen<U+00ED>'' of the [[Police of the Czech Republic|Czech National Police]] uses P90s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://74.125.93.132/search?q=cache:loP28my1wiIJ:www.rokovania.sk/appl/material.nsf/0/A80FC769912BE088C12572EA0049AAD5/%24FILE/vlastnymat.rtf+%C3%9Atvar+osobitn%C3%A9ho+ur%C4%8Denia+p90&cd=3&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us |title=Jednotka Zvl<U+00E1><U+0161>tnych Zahrani<U+010D>n<U+00FD>ch <U+010D>innost<U+00ED> (Unit of Foreign Special Operations) |year=January 10, 2008 |language=Czech |publisher=<U+00DA>rad Vlady Slovenskej Republiky (Cabinet Office of Slovak Republic) Official Website |accessdate=2009-09-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://is.muni.cz/th/176198/fsps_b/Bakalarska_prace.txt |title=Speci<U+00E1>ln<U+00ED> V<U+00FD>cvik Zvl<U+00E1><U+0161>tn<U+00ED>ch Policejn<U+00ED>ch Jednotek <U+00DA>RN |language=Czech |publisher=Ve<U+0159>ejn<U+00E9> slu<U+017E>by Informa<U+010D>n<U+00ED>ho syst<U+00E9>mu (Public Services Information System) |accessdate=2009-09-29}}</ref>

* {{flag|Dominican Republic}}: The Dominican Republic's counter-terrorist group purchased 150 P90s to replace their [[Uzi]]s in 2002.<ref name="lalibrebelgique">Cf. Raf Sauviller, l.c. (2004). <U+201C>Le Registre est un nid <U+00E0> Probl<U+00E8>mes&nbsp;<U+2013> Des P90 de la FN ont <U+00E9>t<U+00E9> Livr<U+00E9>sau Surinam et en R<U+00E9>publique Dominicaine: de quoi se Scandaliser?<U+201D> (in French). La Libre Belgique, 26/8/2002.</ref> The [[Military of the Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic Armed Forces]] and ''Cuerpo de Ayudantes Militares del Presidente de la Rep<U+00FA>blica'' use the P90 for various roles<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dominicanoshoy.com/articulos/articulo/yerno-del-presidente-tendria-mas-problemas-por-porte-arma-de-guerra |title=Karin en Problemas por Porte Arma de Guerra |year=December 02, 2008 |language=Spanish |publisher=http://dominicanoshoy.com&nbsp;<U+2014> Dominicanos Hoy (Dominican Today) News Online |accessdate=2009-10-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dominicanoshoy.com/articulos/articulo/advierten-karin-se-escuda-en-vinculos-con-presidente-para-bellaquerias |title=Advierten Karin se Escuda en V<U+00ED>nculos con Presidente |year=December 04, 2008 |language=Spanish |publisher=http://dominicanoshoy.com&nbsp;<U+2014> Dominicanos Hoy (Dominican Today) News Online |accessdate=2009-10-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dominicanoshoy.com/articulos/articulo/tribunal-conocera-medidas-de-coercion-contra-carim |title=Tribunal Conocer<U+00E1> Medidas de Coerci<U+00F3>n Contra Carim |year=August 14, 2009 |language=Spanish |publisher=http://dominicanoshoy.com&nbsp;<U+2014> Dominicanos Hoy (Dominican Today) News Online |accessdate=2009-10-15}}</ref>

* {{flag|El Salvador}}: The ''[[Comando Especial Anti-Terrorista|Comando Especial Antiterrorista]]'' purchased 350 P90s to replace their older [[FNC|FN FNC]] assault rifles in 2002.<ref>Montes, Julio (2003). <U+201C>Unidades de <U+00E9>lite en Centroam<U+00E9>rica<U+201D> (in Spanish). Tecnolog<U+00ED>a Militar, 2003. N. 4, pp.16-20.</ref>

* {{flag|France}}:  The [[GIGN]] counter-terrorism group of the ''[[French Gendarmerie|Gendarmerie Nationale]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://le.cos.free.fr/new-GIGN.htm |title=Nouvelles Tenues et Nouveaux Moyens pour le GIGN |language=French |accessdate=2008-10-27 |work=Les Forces Speciales en Action...}}</ref><ref>Micheletti, Eric. "GIGN 30 Ans d'Operations" (in French). RAIDS Magazine (May 2004), N<U+00B0> 216.</ref><ref>Micheletti, Eric. "Le GIGN Aujourd'hui" (in French). Histoire & Collections (September 30, 2004). ISBN 978-2913903944.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aresworldefense.com/ares/pdf/8pdf.html |title=Mas Capacidad para el GIGN Frances |year=March 2008 |language=Spanish |publisher=http://aresworldefense.com&nbsp;<U+2014> Ares Worldefense Magazine Online |accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref> and the [[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion|RAID]] unit of the ''[[Police Nationale]]'' use P90s.<ref>S<U+00FC>nkler, S<U+00F6>ren (May 2009). "Das Spezialeinsatzkommando RAID" (in German). Caliber Magazine (ISSN 0933-3738).</ref><ref>Micheletti, Eric. "Le RAID En Action" (in French). RAIDS Magazine (2005), Hors-s<U+00E9>rie N<U+00B0> 19.</ref><ref>Collectif. "Le RAID: Unit<U+00E9> d'<U+00E9>lite de la Police Nationale" (in French). Cr<U+00E9>pin-Leblond (September 15, 2005). ISBN 978-2703002642.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.agentura.ru/dossier/france/police |title=<U+041F><U+043E><U+043B><U+0438><U+0446><U+0435><U+0439><U+0441><U+043A><U+0438><U+0439> <U+0441><U+043F><U+0435><U+0446><U+043D><U+0430><U+0437>&nbsp;<U+2014> <U+041F><U+043E><U+0434><U+0440><U+0430><U+0437><U+0434><U+0435><U+043B><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+044F> RAID & GIPN (Police Commandos&nbsp;<U+2014> RAID & GIPN Departments) |author=Mokeev, Sanjar |year=May 06, 2003 |language=Russian |publisher=http://agentura.ru&nbsp;<U+2014> Agentura.ru Intelligence and Terrorism Journalism Hub |accessdate=2009-10-21}}</ref> The [[Commandement des Op<U+00E9>rations Sp<U+00E9>ciales|COS]] special operations group<ref name="diez2000"/> and some specialized units within the [[French Army]], such as the ''[[Troupes de marine]]'' naval infantry regiment and ''[[1er R<U+00E9>giment Parachutiste d'Infanterie de Marine]]'', use P90s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defense.gouv.fr/terre/decouverte/materiels/materiels_specifiques/p90 |title=Terre&nbsp;<U+2014> P90 |language=French |publisher=Official Website of the French Gendarmerie Nationale |date= |accessdate=2009-03-13}}</ref>

* {{flag|Germany}}: The [[Federal Criminal Police Office (Germany)|BKA]] ''Sicherungsgruppe'' use P90s for dignitary protection duties.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}

* {{flag|Greece}}: The [[Hellenic Coast Guard|Coast Guard]] and the [[Special Anti-Terrorist Unit|EKAM]] counter-terrorist unit of the [[Hellenic Police]] use P90s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kalibar.rs/code/navigate.php?Id=74 |title=Trojanski Konj za Teroriste |language=Serbian |author=Milosevic, Milan |year=2005 |publisher=Kalibar |accessdate=2009-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astynomia.gr/images/stories/DOCS/Attachment11480_ENHMEROTIKO_EKAM_ENGL.pdf |title=Greece Ministry of Public Order Press Office: Special Anti-Terrorist Unit |year=July 2004 |publisher=http://astynomia.gr&nbsp;<U+2014> Official Website of the Hellenic Police |accessdate=2009-09-27}}</ref><ref>"EKAM: Athens' Specialist Force" (June 01, 2004). Intersec UK Magazine (ISSN: 09630058), Volume 14 Issue 6, pp 182.</ref><ref>Meyr, Eitan (December, 2005). "The Elite EKAM: Counter-Terrorism Greek Style". Aviation Security International (ISSN 1352-0149), Volume 11 Issue 6.</ref>

